      "id": "896056426731790",
      "score": 2,
      "review_title": "Kinda boring ngl",
      "review_description": "Saw the videos, thought the game would be peak and funny, bought it, turns out it really boring, it's just gorilla tag but you platform and rip apart balls of rainbow, aside from that, there's not a lot more to it, at least not since last time I played, game got boring to an extent where I haven't played it probably maybe more than a year. It literally lasted on my gallery for a week -_-. Some ideas I have would be making more creative ways to kill whatever those balls are, not just ripping, eating, throwing into dangerous obstacles or to their friends themselves. This doesn't mean the game is bad! If you want to buy it, then do it, it's your money, and everyone has their own opinions and likings. And there was actual effort put into this, too. A cool thing to make skins feel better to get would be making each one have a buit in weapon to kill. I dunno, the fish one being able to shoot a burst of water that work like bullets for example, that would make them more rewarding to get and would give a lot of reasons to get them (Though the advantages are disabled on multiplayer for a fair game)",
